  "slug": "when-the-money-flow-reverses-supporting-your-parents-reading",
  "title": "When the Money Flow Reverses: Supporting Your Parents",
  "subtitle": "The financial, emotional, and relational complexity of becoming the provider for the people who provided for you",
  "excerpt": "A reading on the role reversal of financially supporting ageing parents. Covers the emotional tangle that tends to arrive with the logistics, the common guilt and resentment patterns, and what helps people navigate it with clarity rather than anxiety.",
  "type": "READING",
  "sourceNotes": "Written for homemade.education. Draws on public-domain psychology and financial planning literature on adult children and parental financial support, including gerontological research on family financial dynamics.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "At some point for many women, the financial flow reverses. The people who provided for you begin to need provision. The role reversal carries a specific tangle of guilt, obligation, resentment, and fear, none of which makes you a bad daughter. This reading walks a tapping round, a Release/Allow pair, and a journal-prompt set for the role-shift grief itself.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The feelings that arrive with the logistics",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Guilt about having more than the people who raised you. Obligation, sometimes indistinguishable from love. Resentment that builds quietly when giving is expected rather than chosen. Fear underneath all of it: that supporting them will compromise what you have built, and the further fear that noticing the fear makes you a bad daughter. The emotional complexity is proportionate to the situation.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The practice",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "New to tapping? Read ",
